records.addlTxt:
8:30 AM Prosecuting attorney Angela M Wilson in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Andrew Edward Lisdahl in court, in custody. Attorney Nathan M Cockerham in court for Andrew Edward Lisdahl. 
State calls Brian Souza-Sworn and testifies. Received call on attempt to locate on OWI, described vehicle. Found vehicle, observed it swerving out of lane. Driver was sole occupant, ID'd by license. Witness identifies defendant. 
Att Cockerham objects
Court overruled.
State presents Exhibit #1 Certified driving record WI(M-O-R). Lists prior convictions. Exhibit #2 Certified driving record MN(M-O-R). Moves for bindover
Att Cockerham- no response
Court finds probable cause for bind over. Sets date
Arraignment scheduled for September 2, 2022 at 09:30 am.

No use or possession of alcohol. No operation of a motor vehicle unless Defendant has valid permit or license.

3:00 PM Defendant Andrew Edward Lisdahl appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Chad C La Lor in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Cockerham via video for defendant. Court verifies current address. Attorney Cockerham received complaint, waives reading and requests preliminary on Count 1 and stands mute on Count 2. State requests $2,500 cash bail and conditions of no use or possession of alcohol and no operation of a motor vehicle unless Defendant has valid permit or license. State notes defendant is currently on probation and has a hold. State reviews MN and WI criminal history. Attorney Cockerham notes defendant is a lifelong resident is not opposed to requested conditions. Asks Court to post $500-1,000 cash bail. Court orders $1,500 cash bail and conditions of no use or possession of alcohol and no operation of a motor vehicle unless Defendant has valid permit or license.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 27, 2022 at 08:30 am.
